The paper deals with the problem of rainbow colouring in graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The specific type of graph considered is split graphs, which can be seen as a special case of bipartite graphs, and thus falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the problem, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper involves algorithms and their analysis, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.GT).
